# Pipeline (medallion) standards

## Bronze
- Read raw Parquet from Azure Blob as-is
- Apply schema enforcement only (cast types, rename columns to snake_case)
- Write to Delta Lake table: bronze_{source_name}
- No business logic

## Silver
- Read from Bronze Delta tables
- Apply cleaning: drop nulls on key fields, deduplicate, normalise dates to UTC
- Write to Delta Lake table: silver_{source_name}
- Document every transformation with a comment explaining why

## Gold
- Join Silver tables into business-ready aggregates
- Apply FinBERT sentiment scoring on news headlines here
- Write final output as Delta table: gold_financial_signals
- This is what the .NET API reads from

## Every notebook must have
- A markdown cell at top explaining what the notebook does
- A parameters cell for configurable inputs
- Cell-level comments for non-obvious logic
